Feature 5 – Remove Node, Remove Nodes, and Remove Edge APIs

Three new APIs were added to the Graph class to support removing nodes and edges.

API: removeNode(String label)

This method removes a single node from the graph. It also removes all outgoing edges from that
node and all incoming edges to that node from other nodes. If the specified node does not exist
in the graph, the method throws a NoSuchElementException.

API: removeNodes(String[] labels)

This method removes multiple nodes from the graph by iterating through the provided array and
calling removeNode() for each label. If any node in the array does not exist, a
NoSuchElementException is thrown.

API: removeEdge(String srcLabel, String dstLabel)

This method removes a single directed edge from the source node to the destination node. The
nodes themselves remain in the graph. If either node does not exist, or if the specified edge
does not exist, a NoSuchElementException is thrown.

Test cases cover three scenarios as required by the assignment:

Scenario 1: Nodes and edges are correctly removed.
- testRemoveNode: Parses input1.dot, removes node "a", verifies node count is 7, verifies
  outgoing edges from "a" and incoming edge d->a are removed.
- testRemoveNodes: Removes nodes "f" and "g", verifies node count is 6 and edges e->f
  and e->g are removed.
- testRemoveEdge: Removes edge a->b, verifies edge count decreases by 1 while both
  nodes "a" and "b" still exist.

Scenario 2: Removing non-existent nodes throws exceptions.
- testRemoveNonExistentNode: Attempts to remove node "z" from a graph that only
  contains node "a". Verifies NoSuchElementException is thrown.
- testRemoveNodesOneNonExistent: Attempts to remove ["a", "nonexistent"]. Verifies
  NoSuchElementException is thrown.

Scenario 3: Removing non-existent edges throws exceptions.
- testRemoveNonExistentEdge: Attempts to remove edge a->c when only a->b exists.
  Verifies NoSuchElementException is thrown.
- testRemoveEdgeWithNonExistentNode: Attempts to remove edge a->z when node "z"
  does not exist. Verifies NoSuchElementException is thrown.

