Feature 7 – BFS Graph Search (bfs branch)

A new branch called "bfs" was created from main to implement a graph search API using the
Breadth-First Search algorithm.

API: Path GraphSearch(String src, String dst)

This method finds a path from a source node to a destination node using BFS. It uses a Queue
(LinkedList) to explore nodes level by level. A parent map tracks the path from source to
destination. If a path exists, the method reconstructs it and returns a Path object. If no path
exists, or if either node is not in the graph, the method returns null.

A new Path class was created to represent a path through the graph. The Path class stores an
ordered list of node labels and provides a toString() method that formats the path as
n1 -> n2 -> n3.

Test cases for BFS:
- testBFSPathExists: Searches from "a" to "h" in input1.dot. Verifies a path is found that
  starts at "a" and ends at "h".
- testBFSPathNotExists: Searches from "h" to "a". Since "h" has no outgoing edges, verifies
  null is returned.
- testBFSSameNode: Searches from "a" to "a". Verifies a path of length 1 is returned.
- testBFSNodeNotInGraph: Searches from "a" to "z" where "z" does not exist. Verifies null
  is returned.

