Feature 8 – DFS Graph Search (dfs branch)

A new branch called "dfs" was created from main to implement the same graph search API using
the Depth-First Search algorithm.

API: Path GraphSearch(String src, String dst)

This method finds a path from a source node to a destination node using DFS. It uses a Stack
instead of a Queue to explore nodes depth-first. The parent map and path reconstruction logic
are identical to the BFS implementation. If a path exists, the method returns a Path object. If
no path exists, or if either node is not in the graph, the method returns null.

