Feature 9 – Merge BFS and DFS Branches with Conflict Resolution

The bfs branch was first merged into main cleanly. Then the dfs branch was merged into main,
which produced a merge conflict in Graph.java and GraphTest.java because both branches
added a GraphSearch method with the same signature but different implementations.

The conflict was resolved by introducing a new Algorithm enum and changing the method
signature to accept a third parameter for choosing the search algorithm.

New file: Algorithm.java

    public enum Algorithm {
        BFS,
        DFS
    }

Updated API: Path GraphSearch(String src, String dst, Algorithm algo)

This unified method finds a path from src to dst using the specified algorithm. Internally, it
uses a Deque as the data structure. When Algorithm.BFS is specified, nodes are removed from
the front of the deque (queue behavior). When Algorithm.DFS is specified, nodes are removed
from the back of the deque (stack behavior).

Example usage:

    Graph graph = GraphParser.parseGraph("sample_inputs/input1.dot");
    Path bfsPath = graph.GraphSearch("a", "h", Algorithm.BFS);
    Path dfsPath = graph.GraphSearch("a", "h", Algorithm.DFS);
    System.out.println("BFS: " + bfsPath);  // BFS: a -> e -> f -> h
    System.out.println("DFS: " + dfsPath);  // DFS: a -> e -> g -> h

The final test suite contains 22 tests covering all features from Part 1 and Part 2, including
both BFS and DFS search tests using the Algorithm enum.

